description: Lists the Active Directory identity providers for user-based subscriptions.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: You can use the following filters to streamline results: Product DirectoryId (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return more specific results from a describe or list operation. You can use filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. Attribute (string) --- The name of an attribute to use as a filter. Operation (string) --- The type of search (For example, eq, geq, leq) Value (string) --- Value of the filter.

nested_items.name: IdentityProviderSummaries
nested_items.description: An array of IdentityProviderSummary resources that contain details about the Active Directory identity providers that meet the request criteria.

nested_items.name: FailureMessage
nested_items.description: The failure message associated with an identity provider.

nested_items.name: IdentityProvider
nested_items.description: The IdentityProvider resource contains information about an identity provider.

nested_items.name: ActiveDirectoryIdentityProvider
nested_items.description: The ActiveDirectoryIdentityProvider resource contains settings and other details about a specific Active Directory identity provider.

nested_items.name: ActiveDirectorySettings
nested_items.description: The ActiveDirectorySettings resource contains details about the Active Directory, including network access details such as domain name and IP addresses, and the credential provider for user administration.

nested_items.name: DomainCredentialsProvider
nested_items.description: Points to the CredentialsProvider resource that contains information about the credential provider for user administration.

nested_items.name: SecretsManagerCredentialsProvider
nested_items.description: Identifies the Secrets Manager secret that contains credentials needed for user administration in the Active Directory.

nested_items.name: SecretId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Secrets Manager secret that contains credentials.

nested_items.name: DomainIpv4List
nested_items.description: A list of domain IPv4 addresses that are used for the Active Directory.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: The domain name for the Active Directory.

nested_items.name: DomainNetworkSettings
nested_items.description: The DomainNetworkSettings resource contains an array of subnets that apply for the Active Directory.

nested_items.name: Subnets
nested_items.description: Contains a list of subnets that apply for the Active Directory domain.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ActiveDirectoryType
nested_items.description: The type of Active Directory --- either a self-managed Active Directory or an Amazon Web Services Managed Active Directory.

nested_items.name: DirectoryId
nested_items.description: The directory ID for an Active Directory identity provider.

nested_items.name: IdentityProviderArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the identity provider.

nested_items.name: Product
nested_items.description: The name of the user-based subscription product.

nested_items.name: SecurityGroupId
nested_items.description: A security group ID that allows inbound TCP port 1688 communication between resources in your VPC and the VPC endpoint for activation servers.

nested_items.name: Subnets
nested_items.description: The subnets defined for the registered identity provider.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the identity provider.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The next token used for paginated responses. When this field isn't empty, there are additional elements that the service hasn't included in this request. Use this token with the next request to retrieve additional objects.
